Week 3

Subsetting and Sorting

set.seed(13435)
X <- data.frame(
  "var1" = sample(1:5),
  "var2" = sample(6:10),
  "var3" = sample(11:15)
)
X <- X[sample(1:5),]
X$var2[c(1,3)] <- NA
X
X <- data.frame(
  var1 = c(2, 1, 3, 5, 4),
  var2 = c(NA, 10, NA, 6, 9),
  var3 = c(15, 11, 12, 14, 13)
)
X
X[,1]
[1] 2 1 3 5 4
X[,"var1"]
[1] 2 1 3 5 4
X[1:2, "var2"]
[1] NA 10
X[(X$var1 <= 3 & X$var3 > 11),]
X[(X$var1 <= 3 | X$var3 > 15),]
X[which(X$var2 > 8),]
sort(X$var1)
[1] 1 2 3 4 5
sort(X$var1, decreasing = TRUE)
[1] 5 4 3 2 1
sort(X$var2, na.last = TRUE)
[1]  6  9 10 NA NA
X[order(X$var1),]
X[order(X$var1, X$var3),]
